<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05011n"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05011n">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05011n"> 11(n)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Extremes head &amp; tail meet</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">This is the reason why the number seven appears and reappears in religious systems. It is found among savages, and among the European votaries of oriental mysticism who talk of the seven-fold nature of man. Thus religion is like the mythical snake of eternity. <mark>Extremes meet; the head and the tail are united</mark>. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [The Creation Story] 18-19</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n10004a" href="n10all.htm#n10004a">N10 (VI.B.16):004(a)</a> </mm> </dd></dl>
